{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐκμαίνω</b>, <br /> <b>drive mad</b> with passion, ἐκμήνας θυμὸν ἔρωτι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Epigrammata - PLG” 7.6, compare 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 5.91 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐπί τινι <b>with love for</b> her, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ecclesiazusae” 966; φόβῳ τέτρωρον ἐκμαίνων ὄχον 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 1229 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; πόθον ἐκμῆναι <b>to kindle mad</b> desire, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 1142 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐκμῆναί τινα δωμάτων <b>to drive</b> one <b>raving from</b> the house, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 36 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, with <i>perfect</i> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2 \">Refs</a>] <i>active</i> ἐκμέμηνα, <b>go mad</b> with passion, ταῦτα ἐκμαίνεσθαι ἔς τινα <b>rage</b> so against one, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.33, compare 37, 2nd c.AD: Pausanias Periegeta 1.11.15 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἔρωτι οὐρανίῳ ἐκμεμηνυῖα [διάνοια] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Philo Judaeus 1.482 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; of mania, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Aretaeus Medicus “περὶ αἰτιῶν καὶ σημείων χρονίων παθῶν” 1.6; ὑπὸ τοῦ ἀκράτου 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Nigr.” 5 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; of sexual passion, εἰς γυναῖκας ἐκμανείς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus “Antiquitates Judaicae” 8.7.5: also, with _accusative_, ἐκμανῆναί τινα \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<b>to be madly in love with..,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Anacreont. 11.4; τινί 5th c.AD: Aristaenetus Rhetor 1.15 \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>] at Title Page; of persons in delirium, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “ἐπιδημίαι” 3.17.ιγ. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G7119","accentedUnicode":"ἐκμαίνω","shortDef":"to drive mad","mediumDef":"to drive mad","stepGloss":"to drive mad","stepTransliteration":"ekmainō","count":0,"_step_Type":"verb"}]}